TITLE: Throwback tech continues to fascinate us. Do we want an analog future?
SUMMARY: In 2022, we're more plugged in than ever.

TITLE: Exclusive: Jordan king says prepared for conflict if Jerusalem status changes
SUMMARY: Jordan's king says he is prepared for conflict should the status of Jerusalem's holy sites change as Israel prepares to swear in what is likely to be the most right-wing government in its history.

TITLE: Convicted member of plot to kidnap Michigan governor sentenced
SUMMARY: A Michigan federal judge sentenced a man convicted of plotting to kidnap Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer to nearly 20 years in prison Wednesday.

TITLE: Fog blamed for deadly 200-vehicle pileup. See the stunning footage
SUMMARY: The major incident happened on a bridge in the Chinese city of Zhengzhou and was caused by extreme fog, according to Reuters.

TITLE: Buffalo woman meets sister of disabled man she rescued from snowstorm
SUMMARY: Sha'Kyra Aughtry cared for a disabled man in her home until neighbors could transport him to a hospital after finding him severely frostbitten and crying out for help during a deadly winter storm on Christmas Eve. The man's sister, Yvonne White, and Sha'Kyra join CNN This Morning to share their story.

TITLE: Most US flight cancellations are from Southwest
SUMMARY: • Analysis: Why Southwest is melting down

TITLE: Southwest CEO responds to backlash over cancellations
SUMMARY: Southwest Airlines CEO Bob Jordan released an apology to stranded travelers as the beleaguered airline continues to grapple with what US Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg has referred to as a complete "meltdown" of the system. In all, Southwest has canceled more than 15,700 flights since winter weather began disrupting air travel on December 22.

TITLE: United and American cap prices on some cities
SUMMARY: Many Southwest customers have been desperately trying something -- anything -- that will get them back home. But some passengers have been horrified to find other airlines posting last-minute flights to their destinations that can cost thousands of dollars.

TITLE: The president and first lady return to a beloved vacation spot before a consequential 2024 announcement
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden this week returns to St. Croix, one of his and first lady Jill Biden's beloved vacation spots, seeking a final opportunity for rest before what is expected to be a contentious 2023 and reelection run.

TITLE: Biden and his team feeling vindicated
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden spent hours during his first foreign trip behind closed doors, attempting to reassure a shaken group of US allies that America was back. It was clear, he later told advisers, just how much work remained to convince them of the durability of that commitment.

TITLE: George Santos faces growing condemnation for lies as House GOP leadership remains silent
SUMMARY: GOP Rep.-elect George Santos is facing growing condemnation from House Democrats, some of whom have called on him to step aside, and even from some corners of the GOP, with at least one of his fellow incoming Republicans calling for him to face an ethics investigation. House GOP leadership, however, remains silent over revelations that the New York Republican lied about parts of his biography.

TITLE: Opinion: Santos poses a serious risk to the GOP
SUMMARY: What happens when Rep.-elect George Santos of New York goes to Washington, DC, in January will be a real test of today's Republican Party. Does honesty and integrity matter at all? Or is GOP leadership so power-hungry that it will allow a serial fabulist to remain in office despite deceiving the public -- and the voters who elected him -- about key aspects of his biography?

TITLE: He lost to Santos. Hear him weigh in on his opponent's lies
SUMMARY: GOP Rep.-elect George Santos admits to fabricating sections of his resume, including his past work experience and education. Democrat Robert Zimmerman, the candidate who lost to Santos, calls out his former opponent.

TITLE: Supreme Court keeps controversial border restriction in effect
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court said Tuesday that the controversial Trump-era border restriction known as Title 42 will remain in effect while legal challenges play out, a move that ensures that federal officials will be able to continue to swiftly expel migrants at US borders at least for the next several months.

TITLE: Judge orders Kari Lake to compensate Katie Hobbs for some fees
SUMMARY: A Maricopa County judge on Tuesday ordered Arizona Republican Kari Lake to compensate Democratic Gov.-elect Katie Hobbs for some legal fees related to the election lawsuit Lake had brought challenging her loss, but he stopped short of sanctioning Lake for filing the lawsuit.

TITLE: US House bans TikTok from official devices
SUMMARY: TikTok has been banned from electronic devices managed by the US House of Representatives, according to an internal notice sent to House staff.

TITLE: Woman found dead in car was six minutes from home when she got stranded in snow
SUMMARY: • Buffalo woman saves man with severe frostbite after getting him out of storm

TITLE: Trump White House aide told Jan. 6 panel Meadows burned documents a dozen times in transition period
SUMMARY: • Video: Gloria Borger reacts to 'stunning' testimony alleging Meadows burned documents

TITLE: Watch CNN Live
Chelsea Handler reflects on split from Jo Koy
SUMMARY: Chelsea Handler is opening up about her former relationship with fellow comic Jo Koy.

TITLE: 'I need a recovery beer,' Luka Dončić says after making NBA history
SUMMARY: Luka Dončić put up a historic triple-double in the Dallas Mavericks' thrilling 126-121 overtime win over the New York Knicks on Tuesday.

TITLE: The soda market is flat, but not for Dr Pepper
SUMMARY: In the pantheon of sodas, Dr Pepper is the odd one out: It doesn't have the popularity or sales of Coca-Cola or Pepsi, you can't use it in a standard cocktail, and it doesn't fall neatly into a category like cola or root beer.

TITLE: Buccal fat removal procedures being driven by celebrities and social media
SUMMARY: Buccal fat removal might just be the new Brazilian butt lift -- aka the newest cosmetic surgery procedure to take over social media.

TITLE: 'Tradwife' rhetoric is trickling into mainstream
SUMMARY: On certain corners of the internet, a segment of women is exhibiting a nostalgia for an era it has never known.

TITLE: 8-year-old goes viral for incredible dance moves at school concert
SUMMARY: 8-year-old Jaden Williams was caught on camera tearing up the stage at his elementary school winter concert in Menlo Park, California. CNN affiliate KGO has the story.

TITLE: Raging flash flood cascades down cliff as tourists scramble to escape
SUMMARY: Sudden flooding caused immediate evacuation for tourists visiting a World Heritage Site in Petra, Jordan.

TITLE: Mega Millions jackpot now up to $640 million
SUMMARY: No winner emerged in the $565 million Mega Millions jackpot drawing on Tuesday night, and that means some lucky ticket-buyer has a chance of taking home an estimated $640 million ($328 million in cash) in the final Mega Millions drawing of 2022.

TITLE: Opinion: Who will be each party's presidential frontrunner at the end of 2023?
Former Pope Benedict is 'very sick', Francis says
SUMMARY: Pope Francis has said that his predecessor Pope Benedict, the 95-year-old former pontiff who resigned from the post nine years ago, is "very sick" after a deterioration in his health on Wednesday.

TITLE: Iranian woman takes part in international chess tournament without mandatory hijab
SUMMARY: Iranian chess player Sara Khadem, also known as Sarasadat Khademalsharieh, took part in an international tournament without a hijab, Iranian news outlet Jamaran said on Tuesday.

TITLE: Russia dismisses Ukraine's calls for UN Security Council removal
Should you attend that New Year's Eve party?
SUMMARY: At the end of 2020 and 2021, many people greeted the start of the coming year hunkered down due to the risk of Covid-19. But now, New Year's Eve events and celebrations are back in a big way. A lot of people have plans to attend social functions, whether they are crowded festivities with thousands or house parties with a few relatives and friends.

TITLE: As the market for new weight loss drugs soars, people with diabetes pay the price
SUMMARY: The drug that Jeremy Mitchell takes to manage his diabetes, Ozempic, has become a hot new weight loss fad, and now he's having trouble finding it.

TITLE: Lake Michigan is covered in 'ice pancakes' due to extreme cold
SUMMARY: Aerial footage shows ice formations covering Lake Michigan, including a phenomenon only seen if temperatures drop to well below freezing for several days.

TITLE: Analysis: Southwest got billions of dollars in taxpayer aid. Why is its service still a mess?
SUMMARY: When the coronavirus pandemic ground the transportation industry to a screeching halt in early 2020, the US government doled out more than $54 billion in aid to help pay employees and keep the systems from buckling.

TITLE: More than 100,000 along the West Coast are without power
SUMMARY: A strong storm system bringing heavy rain and mountain snow to much of the western United States has left more than 126,000 customers without power as the region braces for more weather woes in the days to come.

TITLE: Crews work to clear roads for responders in Buffalo after storm that left 31 dead in area
SUMMARY: After a deadly winter storm unleashed a fierce blizzard that swept through Buffalo, New York, with calls for help going unanswered, officials say emergency services have been restored and authorities are clearing roadways for first responders and carrying out welfare checks.

TITLE: Top climate and weather stories of 2022
SUMMARY: From a small island in Polynesia to the white-sand beaches of Florida, the planet experienced a dizzying number of climate and extreme weather disasters in 2022.

TITLE: Podcast: Audie Cornish speaks with her peers about what it takes to rebuild trust in the news media
Fentanyl killed their son. Now they're begging parents to understand the dangers
SUMMARY: It was every parent's worst nightmare.

TITLE: Teen dies from fentanyl poisoning after he sought 'pain reliever' on Snapchat
SUMMARY: On December 27, 2020, 17-year-old Zach Didier died from fentanyl poisoning. Didier bought the deadly opioid from a drug dealer he met on Snapchat, thinking it was a pain reliever, according to Didier's parents, Chris and Laura. They open up about the details with CNN's Josh Campbell.

TITLE: Opinion: Parents, here are tips to save your teens
SUMMARY: Pediatricians like me aren't used to our patients dying. Most children and teens are healthy and thrive, and although some might experiment with drugs, teen overdoses are relatively uncommon. A rising threat, however, is forcing all of us -- especially parents -- to grapple with a new reality.

TITLE: 22 ways flying had a bumpy ride in 2022
SUMMARY: It's been another tough year for aviation, as the world returned to flying after the Covid-19 pandemic, only for the industry to be beset by chaos and cancellations. There were silver linings, however, as the industry slowly recovered and progress was made in terms of more environmentally sustainable flying. Here are the highs and lows of what's been a bumpy ride.

TITLE: Cardinals star J.J. Watt says he's retiring
SUMMARY: Arizona Cardinals defensive end J.J. Watt will retire after the 2022 season, the three-time NFL Defensive Player of the Year announced on Tuesday. Watt said he played his "last ever" home game this past Sunday, a 19-16 overtime loss to the Tampa Bay Buccaneers.

TITLE: Students erupt as teacher battles 8th grader in dance-off
SUMMARY: Video captures an intense dance battle between 8th graders and their teacher.

TITLE: Why three robot sisters could be the friendly face of AI
SUMMARY: Artificial intelligence (AI) has become an integral part of our everyday lives, found in everything from social media algorithms to e-commerce and navigation, but not everyone is comfortable with the idea. The key to winning over a skeptical public could be a family of robot "sisters."

TITLE: Wall Street's dirty secret: It's terrible at forecasting stocks
SUMMARY: December is a month full of market predictions for the year to come. Everyone, from economists to analysts to grocers, seems to have a strong feeling about how stocks will behave going forward.

TITLE: $4 gas could return as soon as May, GasBuddy says
SUMMARY: Gas prices will probably be significantly cheaper overall next year. Yet the national average could still climb back above the $4-a-gallon threshold as soon as May, according to GasBuddy projections shared exclusively with CNN.

TITLE: Dog that inspired 'doge' meme is seriously ill
SUMMARY: Kabosu, the internet-famous dog who inspired the "doge" meme and influenced digital culture for a decade, is seriously ill with leukemia and liver disease.

TITLE: Piers Morgan's Twitter account posts offensive tweets before disappearing
SUMMARY: Controversial British television host Piers Morgan's Twitter account sent out explicit, derogatory tweets to his 8.3 million followers Tuesday about the late Queen Elizabeth, singer Ed Sheeran, boxer Andrew Tate and others, before partially disappearing for some users.

Two surprising takes from Trump's tax returns

TITLE: Is no career safe anymore?
SUMMARY: It's long been clear that artificial intelligence (AI) can one day replace many humans working in fields such as customer service, insurance underwriting and manufacturing. Yet, I have long been complacent about my career as a writer. After all, what AI tool could replace the workings of the human brain?

TITLE: Jamie Lee Curtis is 100% right about 'nepo babies'
SUMMARY: Looks like Merriam-Webster got it wrong with its recent choice for 2022's "word of the year." Instead of picking the word "gaslighting," it should've chosen "nepo babies" -- at least based on the passionate debate that term has triggered in the past week.

TITLE: Russia has shouted about escalation long enough
SUMMARY: Almost 10 months into Russia's full-scale invasion, the vital battle for the future of Ukraine is not on the front line.

TITLE: Why I am choosing not to see 'The Whale'
SUMMARY: As Darren Aronofsky's "The Whale" -- which has been in select theaters -- opens in theaters around the country this week, the film could become a powerful empathy generator. Just perhaps not in the way it was intended.

TITLE: The truth some Republicans don't want to hear
SUMMARY: It's no way to run a government. But these days, it's unfortunately the only way to run a government.

TITLE: The January 6 report is a 'mirror test' for Americans
SUMMARY: Late Thursday night, the House select committee investigating the January 6 insurrection released its final report, a bulging 845-page account of a months-long effort to overturn the results of the 2020 presidential election. In its detailed account, the committee shows how former President Donald Trump and his allies — inside and outside of government — used a combination of intimidation, lies, threats of violence and political machinations to attempt to prevent the certification of Joe Biden's election to the presidency.
